  "text": "As has been shown in the case of CDV infection in lions in the Serengeti ecosystem, the virus can circulate in lions even when levels of infection are extremely low and asynchronous to infections found in domestic dogs [CITATION_1] , supporting the hypothesis that CDV infection is likely to persist involving the wider domestic dog population beyond the Serengeti ecosystem and other wildlife species.",
